All Classes

  • All Classes Class Summary Exception Summary 
    Class Description
    DuplicateIdException
    The DuplicateIdException class is an exception that indicates an attempt to create a new product with an ID that already exists in the system.
    InvalidPostCommand
    This exception is thrown to indicate that an invalid POST command was received.
    MissingRequiredFieldsException
    This exception is thrown to indicate that one or more required fields are missing in the data provided.
    NegativePriceException
    This exception is thrown to indicate that a negative price value is not allowed.
    NegativeQuantityException
    This exception is thrown to indicate that a negative quantity value is not allowed.
    Product
    The Product class represents a product with its attributes such as ID, name, description, price, and quantity.
    ProductDatabase
    The ProductDatabase class manages the storage and manipulation of product data.
    ProductNotFoundException
    This exception is thrown to indicate that a product with a specific ID is not found.
    ProductSerializationException
    This exception is thrown to indicate an error during the serialization of a product to JSON format.
    ProductService
    The ProductService class represents the main entry point for the product service application.
    ResponseHandler
    The ResponseHandler class provides utility methods for sending HTTP responses.
